properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 1 at 4:53PM MST until February 2 at 3:00AM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Warning for portions of northern and central Wyoming
Tonight...

.Strong winds aloft and a tight pressure gradient will combine
for high winds across the Absaroka Mountains into the Cody
Foothills into tonight. High winds across southeast Fremont into
Natrona County are likely today as well.

* WHAT...West to northwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 65
mph.

* WHERE...Cody Foothills. The strongest winds will occur just
south of Cody, as well as between Clark and the junction of
Highway 120 and the Chief Joseph Highway.

* WHEN...Until 3 AM MST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation especially along Highway 120.
An enhanced blow over risk for light and high profile vehicles
including camper trailers and semi trucks.
properties.instruction:
Use caution if traveling. Please keep two hands on your steering
wheel in case of a sudden, strong wind gust. In a parking lot,
park into the wind to minimize the possibility of your car door
hitting another parked vehicle.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM MST SUNDAY
